    • Field Detail

      • AUTHORITY_DEFAULT

        public static final String AUTHORITY_DEFAULT
        Content to put in the URI field when adding a new metadata element of type person. This should usually be your preferred norm data file’s URI prefix as to the user doesn’t have to enter it over and over again.

        Example: authority.default=http\://d-nb.info/gnd/

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • AUTHORITY_ID_FROM_URI

        public static final String AUTHORITY_ID_FROM_URI
        Which authority identifier to use for a given URI prefix.

        Example: authority.http\://d-nb.info/gnd/.id=gnd

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • BATCH_DISPLAY_LIMIT

        public static final String BATCH_DISPLAY_LIMIT
        Integer, limits the number of batches showing on the page “Batches”. Defaults to -1 which disables this functionality. If set, only the limited number of batches will be shown, the other batches will be present but hidden and thus cannot be modified and not even be deleted.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CATALOGUE_TIMEOUT

        public static final String CATALOGUE_TIMEOUT
        Milliseconds. Indicates the maximum duration an interaction with a library catalogue may take. Defaults to 30 minutes.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • EXPORT_WITH_IMAGES

        public static final String EXPORT_WITH_IMAGES
        Whether during an export to the DMS the images will be copied. Defaults to true.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • HITLIST_PAGE_SIZE

        public static final String HITLIST_PAGE_SIZE
        Integer. Number of hits to show per page on the hitlist when multiple hits were found on a catalogue search.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • MINIMAL_NUMBER_OF_PAGES

        public static final String MINIMAL_NUMBER_OF_PAGES
        Long. Number of pages per process below which the features in the granualarity dialog shall be locked.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PAGE_SEPARATORS

        public static final String PAGE_SEPARATORS
        Comma-separated list of Strings which may be enclosed in double quotes. Separators available for double page pagination modes.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PLUGIN_FOLDER

        public static final String PLUGIN_FOLDER
        Points to a folder on the file system that contains Production plug-in jars. In the folder, there must be subfolders named as defined in enum PluginType (currently: “import”, “step”, “validation”, “command” and “opac”) in which the plug-in jars must be stored.

        Must be terminated by the file separator.

        See Also:
        PluginType, Constant Field Values

      • PLUGIN_TEMP_DIR

        public static final String PLUGIN_TEMP_DIR
        Points to a folder on the file system that plug-ins may use to write temporary files.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • USE_METADATA_ENRICHMENT

        public static final String USE_METADATA_ENRICHMENT
        Boolean. Set to true to enable the feature of automatic meta data inheritance and enrichment. If this is enabled, all meta data elements from a higher level of the logical document structure are automatically inherited and lower levels are enriched with them upon process creation, given they have the same meta data type addable. Defaults to false.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • WITH_AUTOMATIC_PAGINATION

        public static final String WITH_AUTOMATIC_PAGINATION
        Boolean. Set to false to disable automatic pagination changes in the metadata editor. If false, pagination must be updated manually by clicking the link “Read in pagination from images”.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
